#. <section class="sutta" id="sn48.4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn48.4:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 48"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 48"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.4:0.2"
msgid "1. Suddhikavagga"
msgstr "1. Plain Version"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 4. Paṭhamaarahantasutta → arahaṃ 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn48.4:0.3"
msgid "4. Paṭhamaarahantasutta"
msgstr "4. A Perfected One (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.4:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, indriyāni."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five faculties."

msgctxt "sn48.4:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn48.4:1.3"
msgid ""
"Saddhindriyaṃ, vīriyindriyaṃ, satindriyaṃ, samādhindriyaṃ, paññindriyaṃ."
msgstr "The faculties of faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom."

#. VAR: imesaṃ pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ assādañca → samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn48.4:1.4"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako imesaṃ pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ assādañca "
"ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ viditvā anupādāvimutto hoti—"
msgstr ""
"A noble disciple comes to be freed by not grasping after truly understanding "
"these five faculties’ gratification, drawback, and escape."

msgctxt "sn48.4:1.5"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo "
"ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto”ti."
msgstr ""
"Such a mendicant is called a perfected one, with defilements ended, who has "
"completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the "
"burden, achieved their own goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and "
"is rightly freed through enlightenment.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn48.4:1.6"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
